Now for the actual report,<br />
First Game<br />
Jonathan Richer(1500) Archery/Easterling Corruption,<br />
I bid 2 to his 1 and start, so I am at 1 burden thanks to pipin, I got sam an hobbit sword for him and a promise I think, he plays one burden adder with a polearm  wich takes one archery and gives a wound to sam and I double pretty easily to 3. his start his Arwen Doe and greenleaf so I am prety concerned cause I think it is a very bad matchup for me but he happens to draw no double shot and no elven bow all game long...when he moves to 5 with like 2 burdens I Play captain with Army a couple of burden adders and a skirmisher I use army&#39;s and captain&#39;s text to kill 3 of his 5 companions so in the fierce frodo has to fight with only Izzy&#39;s bane and sting so he dies to both since the army has bow +  polearm giving me plenty of pool.<br />
Good: I had great draws early giving me 3 burdens when he moved to 5, awesome job done by the site 5, great opponent<br />
Bad; he got bad draws all game long that wasn&#39;t really fun I guess but he managed to keep smiling and have fun...<br />
Ugly: adding like 3-4 burdens at site 5 with the sites, text Vision from afar and the guard<br />
FW(3)<br />
<br />
Second Matchup<br />
Julien Vasquez(1668) Elves and men Archery(?)/uruk beatdown<br />
we both bid 2 and both roll a one on the die, second time another one for me to his 2 so he starts, he gets gorn with bow pretty early and I have a bad time adding burdens, when I&#39;m at 4 I give zillions of pool and he gets me an uruk captain and lurtz along eith saruman SOTE, he maages to kill both my unbound hobbitses in the process but at that point I have gorn outfor an unkown reason...I might have killed my pipin before that. when I move to 5 I have 4 burdens and a killer shadow hand but he plays enquea so I must discard my hand or lose a couple companions so I dicards like 2 Visions from afar, 2 captains, my lone enquea and a lieutnant. so that&#39;s pretty bad since he&#39;s like 2 sites in front of me too and haves only 2 burdens, he moves to 8 I play my last captain with polearm ad 2-3 other guys but frodo is like 2-3 strenght from being overhelmed and I kill every body cause of pump by the captain and small hope but gorn survives exausted and frodo wit 4 burdens I think, I survive a site cycling as much as I can with sam but then draw the last 3 cards of my pile...I only have an easterling lieutnant with 2 bows and a polearm so that&#39;s game (he played boromir too)<br />
Good: killing Greenleaf, Faramir and Pipin at sit 8 very cool opponent<br />
Bad; adding like 2 burdens the whole game<br />
Ugly: best hand I could imagine in the discard cause of the site + enquea on the table...<br />
FL(4)<br />
<br />
here is the lunch break so I go to the nearby burger king with Serge who came from Joliette and a couple of others. ate too much and too fast + drinking way too much coke...<br />
<br />
Matthew (1629) stupid swarms with isen regroup wounding/elf + gimli<br />
I have very few details from this game since I was very preocupied with not being overhelmed at every site and keeping my coke in my body...so I play like sam a promise there and back again and a talent then moves, he plays an isen orc and a saroooman&#39;s power :(. I survive pretty easily taking a couple of wound and stopping, it took really long to Matthew to draw an elven bow or legolas so I had already added some burdens to the zero he bid but he had like 3 cards on both gimli and arwen at site 3 but I play no grima oubviously he moves to 7 giving me lost of pol and having like 5-6 burdens I play enquea and a couple easterling killing arwen in maneuver spreading threats and killing everyone but frodo in skirmishes caus I pumps my skirmisher until I overhelm frodo but he paths me :( army with polearm is jsut plain nasty with that many burdens. now it&#39;s my turn, I still have frodo with sword, sam with sword legolas with toys I have like 3 wound on frodo none one legolas and sam, he played a huge amount of minions including several exert to wound ones and discard to wound ones..there is like 5 minions on frodo  1 on sam and one on legolas, he had to put the all on frodo otherwise I would have survived with him...so frodo bites it and passes the ring to sam, I take like 7 wounds in regroup leaving me with only sam exausted but it doesn&#39;t matter cause I have a really awesome shadow hand and he haves 7 burdens, h epays very few things so it takes me like 12 to overhelm frodo I get captain with polearm, skirmisher with polearm and 2 other easterling ...Game<br />
Good; great opponent, shadow did fairly well <br />
bad: First time I ever passed the ring to sam, 2 saroooman&#39;s power clearing me like 3 or 4 promises :(<br />
Ugly: both of us with lone ringbearers at the end and me swarming with shredder guys<br />
FW(7)<br />
<br />
Fourth matchup<br />
Matthew Yakobina(1792)Rohan/threat Naz<br />
than was a funny game we both bid 2 and we roll a 20 sided dice, he got 20 so i&#39;m like well i&#39;ll roll anyway but I think he win that roll...and surprisingly I got my 3rd 1 of the day in 3 rolls :( the die didn&#39;t rolled for me today...<br />
well for the game is was joke over joke with nothing too serious but I did manage to et burdens piled pretty fast cause I had like 2 lT&#39;s and one guard in oppening hand, I move to 2 playing only the bow of te G facing lone toldea I take 2 on lego then stops he,s already at 3...<br />
he moves from there but I manage to get him some more burdens and he&#39;s now desperate to get his Sam Son of hamfast(he at 5-6 burdens)I move at 3 giving him like 8, he may play the king but instead he pulls cycling gollum for 4(2 for captured by the ring) to cycle like 3 Morgul kings black steeds and stuff from his clogged hand but I have to use merry&#39;s text twice to keep lego alive. he moves to 5 ditching his hand and getting 1 more burden from gollum i think, i move to 4 without trouble, he moves to 6 with eomer exausted and eowyn with one wound but he transfes all eomer&#39;s stuff on frsh theoden giving me loads of pool, I pay captain with 3 skirmisher and enquea along with a polearms and gollum I think, I kill both eomer and eowyn with enquea. i&#39;m like 2 twillight short of overhelming frodo cause I played a vision to add a burden  , he kills 2 skirmishers with greenleaf but frodo still had to fight and he was exausted with like 8 burdens (grass ring)  so he could not fight since there was like still 15 in the pool so anyone fighting frodo wins thus kill frodo, I couls have overhelmed anyone with captain&#39;s text and gollum was about sure to win and add a burden so it&#39;s game<br />
Good: AWESOME shadow draws at the start of the game<br />
VERY fun Game, freeps surviving against nazgul(i was pretty surprised)<br />
killing both Eomer and Eowyn with Enquea<br />
Bad; him with major hand clogg looking for sam at site 3 with already 4 burdens<br />
Ugly:me choking alot playing close to nothing an with a talent w/ 4 hobbits<br />
me losing pip for nothing merry had escape and no pool left.  <br />
FW(10)<br />
